# MAGIC ## 2. The problem, in your words
# MAGIC
# MAGIC - **Config-driven** selection of 3 notebooks per study (feature → matching → model). ✅ Great instinct — keep it.
# MAGIC - **If/else condition task per candidate notebook** to route the flow. ⚠️ This is what doesn't scale.
# MAGIC - Model routing gets **copy-pasted under every matching branch** (a converging task can't
# MAGIC   read a value from a sibling branch that was skipped) → an **`M × N` blowup**.
# MAGIC - No clean **study-level fan-out** — today it's effectively one study per run, or the
# MAGIC   whole graph duplicated.
# MAGIC
# MAGIC Keep what's working (config-driven, clear pass/fail gates). Fix only the wiring.

