# MAGIC %md
# MAGIC ## 8. Anticipated questions (and honest answers)
# MAGIC
# MAGIC **"Does DABs cost extra?"** No — DABs is a free packaging/deploy layer (CLI + YAML). You
# MAGIC pay for the **same job compute** you pay for today; nothing is added by the bundle itself.
# MAGIC
# MAGIC **"What are the trade-offs / cons of moving to DABs?"** Be straight:
# MAGIC - It's a **deploy/packaging layer, not a runtime engine** — it won't make jobs faster or
# MAGIC   cheaper by itself.
# MAGIC - There's a **learning curve** (YAML schema, CLI, `deploy`/`run` workflow) and a shift to
# MAGIC   a **code-first** dev loop vs. clicking in the UI.
# MAGIC - You manage **bundle state / deployment discipline** (deploy before run, target
# MAGIC   selection). Minor, but real.
# MAGIC - It does **not** by itself fix branching — the `for_each`/config pattern does (see §5).
# MAGIC
# MAGIC **"Will this change our notebooks or our pass/fail logic?"** No. Same notebooks, same
# MAGIC quality-gate logic. We add `dbutils.widgets` so the job can pass parameters in, and move
# MAGIC selection into the config + a parameter. SLAs and results are unchanged.
# MAGIC
# MAGIC **"Can `for_each` really handle our volume / millions of rows per study?"** `for_each`
# MAGIC handles the **study-level** fan-out and parallelism; the heavy per-study data work still
# MAGIC runs in Spark inside each notebook exactly as today. Concurrency is a dial.
# MAGIC
# MAGIC **"Where does AI help?"** Databricks Assistant / Genie can scaffold the bundle, generate
# MAGIC the `databricks.yml`, and parameterize existing notebooks — a fast on-ramp from your
# MAGIC current POC. (Your team's already using Genie code to build the notebooks.)
# MAGIC
# MAGIC **"How do we migrate without disruption?"** Incrementally: (1) parameterize the existing
# MAGIC matching/model notebooks, (2) collapse the per-method tasks into one dispatcher each,
# MAGIC (3) wrap the per-study pipeline and add `for_each`, (4) package as a DAB for dev/test/prod.
# MAGIC Each step is independently shippable.

